title: For Sale/Trade:  K98 w/ waffenamts

A K98 made by the Mauser arsenal in 1944. Waffenamts are intact and undamaged, rare for some of these old Nazi Germany rifles.
ValueMyStuff has appraised this rifle at 900-1100 dollars, citing it as an all correct late war parts rifle, and a nice example of a late war K98.
A bayonet is included with the rifle.

No, not all numbers match (Only receiver and both barrel bands). This is entirely normal for late war rifles. Towards the end of the war, Germans were repairing their rifles with any parts they could. You're more likely to win the lottery than find a late war K98 with waffenamts, no capture or import mark, no defacing of the waffenamts, and in good shape.
No, it is also not a Russian capture.

title: For Sale:  NIB Colt 1911 Sam Colt Birthday Bicentennial Special  Edition
postcontent: This is a Colt 1991 style 1911 Samuel Colt birthday bicentennial anniversary edition. This gun was produced for the 200th anniversary of the birthday of Samuel Colt (1814-2014). There are other editions made for this anniversary by distributors such as Lew Horton, but this edition was made and distributed only by Colt. This gun was offered for sale directly through Colt 3 specific times: first at the Sam Colt bicentennial birthday celebration, then to Colt employees only, then at the Colt Collectors Association annual convention and that's it. It was planned that 200 would be made, but less than 150 were produced! Very rare gun. Get this one while you can. This gun is in perfect new condition-never fired, never even racked the slide back, only taken out of the box to take pictures, otherwise stored in its box in a safe with other collectibles. Still has original protective oil on it. This gun is blued with gold inlays and scrollwork engraving on the slide, special grips with the Colt coat of arms, and a special serial number (xxxSCOLT200). title: For Sale/Trade:  1944 PU Sniper
postcontent:
For sale/For trade:
1944 Mosin 91/30 PU Sniper from the Izhevsk arsenal. 
The 91/30 PU sniper rifle is an upgrade of the standard Model 91/30 rifle. The functional and robust bolt and magazine remained essentially unchanged except for the bent bolt which allowed it to clear the scope so a round could be easily chambered. The sniper rifles were highly respected for being very rugged, reliable, accurate, and easy to maintain.
The 91/30 PU's were generally built to more exacting standards than their standard issue counterparts. The standard M91/30's were thought to have been fired and the best of the lot were selected to become sniper rifles. Once selected the triggers were reworked and the finish on the later PU snipers were better than the standard infantry rifles.
This rifle is in wartime stock, has an original 1944 scope and mount. Been refurbished, as most have, and the numbers on the magazine is lined out (forced matched), looks to been done at the refurbishing arsenal (Russian letters with numbers). Optics are very clear. Fun and accurate to shoot. 
$850
Kansas City Kansas

postcontent: This Steyr Mannlicher Luxxus 270 winchester is in excellent condition.  Has single set trigger, 3 round magazine, quick release scope mounts, butter handle bolt, excellent blueing, and only a few small dings from the safe.  The picture shows the rifle with a Zeiss scope which DOES NOT COME WITH THE RIFLE. It does come with the ORIGINAL MANNLICHER 3-9x40 scope with a plex reticle and pure clear glass.  This rifle shoots extremely well, prefers top flite ammunition such as Federal Premium, Hornady GMX, or Sako Hammerhead.  Does not do well with Winchester ammunition of any type--do not know why that is but it just doesn't like Winchester ammo.  Does fine with premium Remington ammunition including the classic core-lokt bullets.  Does not seem to care whether it is 130,140, or 150 grain bullets--shoots all of them well.  Has a good recoil pad, and is heavy enough to help absorb standard 270 win recoil.  Also,will shoot both Remington and Hornady reduced recoil ammuntion very accurately, out to factor specified 200 yards without difficulty.  With a tripod rest, can easily be used by women and younger shooters when using the reduced recoil ammunition.  An excellent rifle with outstanding features and high quality throughout.  You will not see this kind of rifle again except at astronomical prices.
